# Bogorodskoye, Meleuzovsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Bogorodskoye () is a rural locality (a village) and the administrative centre of Denisovsky Selsoviet, Meleuzovsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 508 as of 2010. There are 6 streets.
Geography
Bogorodskoye is located 26&nbsp;km northwest of Meleuz (the district's administrative centre) by road. Mikhaylovka is the nearest rural locality.
